		   <br /><nobr><span id="notbold">Score</span>: Default [2.00]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Anonymous&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>I've been camping the bandits behind the bandit hill in West Karanas for a while now.<br><br>Primary benefits:<br><br>1) Bandit sashes.&nbsp;&nbsp;This is a great quest for both exp and loot.  Turning them in to Chesguard at Qeynos pally guild will get you a bronze weap, gold, silver, and good exp.<br><br>2) Bronze weapons.  Quite often the bandits will have bronze spears, bronze main gauches, etc.<br><br>3) Coin.  I usually loot several gold off the bandits.<br><br>4) Exp.  These guys give excellent exp for this level range!<br><br>5) Not usually camped.<br><br>Strategy: <br><br>1) Wait until camp is fully popped and then harmonize.  Usually takes two or three casts.  I wait until the camp is fully popped so I don't get any nasty surprises after I snare a bandit.  <br><br>2) Pick a human bandit and snare it.  Human is important because the other races don't have the bandit sashes.<br><br>3) Run to the west and cast ignite until bandit dies or you run out of mana.  Melee if necessary.<br><br>If you happen to pull two bandits instead of just one with your snare, don't worry.  One is snared already.  Just run off a bit, snare the second one, and hightail it over to the Qhills zone.<br><br>Have fun!</p></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tr><td id="fs8"></td><td align="right" id="fs8" >1 Replies</td></tr></table>
